text: Melicope cinerea is a species of plant in the family Rutaceae known by the common name manena. It is endemic to the Hawaiian Islands. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== cinerea Category:Endemic flora of Hawaii Category:Biota of Maui Category:Biota of Oahu Category:Trees of Hawaii Category:Waianae Range Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
